f=Governance/sentinel/custom/constitution-watch/SKILL.md · in=constitution-watch proactive half constitutional enforcement: board's constitution-enforcement rules decisions *submitted* gate, skill continuously samples outputs actions agents constitutional boundary approaches catching drift violations work never asked review. Warnings near-boundary behavior; freeze-and-escalate clear violations. · p=constitution enforced gate protects gated decisions. what agents daily drafts, recommendations, communications, spend-adjacent actions never passes through board, constitutional erosion happens exactly there: output slightly closer line, none reviewed. skill smoke detector: cheap, always on, loud early rather precise late. · wu=Triggers: "compliance sweep," "constitution check recent work," primarily configured recurring cadence (continuous/daily design; practice, `sweep_cadence` sentinel's config, operator's scheduled runs until automation exists). for: ruling submitted decision (board's constitution-enforcement), auditing whether decisions skipped gate (gate-bypass-detection). · st:/ Protocol=`Load the constitution + derive violation patterns (per article, from its operational test) \· -> Sample recent agent outputs/actions per the configured cadence and scope \· -> Classify each sampled item: CLEAR / NEAR-BOUNDARY / VIOLATION \· -> NEAR-BOUNDARY → warn the producing agent's operator context + log \· -> VIOLATION → freeze recommendation + immediate escalation to board & operator` · h3:Phase Derive Patterns=constitution (same configured path board): article, derive observable violation patterns operational test what output *look like* approached crossed article? Patterns documented article re-derived whenever constitution changes version. constitution stop, board's skill: nothing watch for. · h3:Phase 2 — Sample=Sample recent outputs/actions across agents `sweep_cadence` `sweep_scope` (which output stores/logs read config). Sampling, total review: breadth regularity over depth. Record what sampled coverage gaps visible. · h3:Phase 3 — Classify=**CLEAR** article approached. Logged aggregate (counts, content)., **NEAR-BOUNDARY** approaches article's line without crossing (e.g., draft commitment under categorical limit, language edging toward banned representation). Judgment call, made conservatively: unsure between CLEAR NEAR-BOUNDARY, choose NEAR-BOUNDARY., **VIOLATION** article's operational test met sampled item. unsure between NEAR-BOUNDARY VIOLATION, classify NEAR-BOUNDARY *and* escalate ambiguity board sentinel warns cheaply, violation call triggers freezes right. · h3:Phase 4 — Act=**NEAR-BOUNDARY** warning producing agent's context operator: article quoted, approaching element named, action forced. Warnings logged; three warnings article/agent pattern escalate board drift finding., **VIOLATION** **freeze recommendation**: affected output/action proceed propagate until board rules. Sentinel cannot technically freeze anything itself issues freeze recommendation operator (who actually stop things) simultaneously escalates board's constitution-enforcement formal ruling. Escalation immediate, batched next sweep report. · h3:Phase Log Report=sweep produces report (sampled scope, counts class, warnings issued, escalations); warning escalation audit-trail event audit-trail-design's schema (who/what/when/basis, append-only). Sweep reports over time drift curve trending near-boundary counts early signal even nothing ever crosses. · of=`## Constitution Sweep: [date / cadence window] \·  \· **Constitution version:** [loaded] \· **Scope sampled:** [stores/agents, N items] \·  \· \| Class \| Count \| Items (near-boundary and violations only) \|` · pr=**Proactive, gated.** skill exists work never asks permission., **Warn cheaply, escalate carefully.** NEAR-BOUNDARY deliberately easy trigger; VIOLATION triggers freezes meet article's actual test., **Sentinel recommends freezes; freezes nothing.** operator holds stop button; board holds ruling., **Sample honestly.** Coverage recorded; sweep samples easy stores false comfort., **Trends findings.** Rising near-boundary counts get reported even single item crosses., **No constitution, watch.** board: patterns derive written articles, never inferred values. · f=constitution stop; note enforcement *and* watch dormant until operator writes one., Sweep scope unset sweep whatever operator hands over per-run, flag config gap partial watch beats none, stated partial., Ambiguous classification conservative class escalate ambiguity (Phase rule)., Output stores unreadable sweep time report coverage gap explicitly; never mark unsampled CLEAR. · b:with Other sentinel Skills=`audit-trail-design` defines logging practices skill's events follow; skill producer audit events, designer trails., `gate-bypass-detection` audits *decisions skipped gate*; skill watches *content outputs* against articles. sampled item looks like ungated qualifying decision gets handed gate-bypass-detection., Boundary board: sentinel detects escalates; board rules (constitution-enforcement). Sentinel never issues PASS/VIOLATION rulings "VIOLATION" classification escalation trigger, board's formal ruling supersedes it.